Class UploadQueue

java.lang.Object
  edu.uml.cs.isense.queue.UploadQueue
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class UploadQueue
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

Class that represents the queue of data sets. This object can be instantiated, have data sets added to it, and be rebuilt at any time from the serializable file it is stored on. In order to use the iSENSE-Imports-Queue-Saving technology, an UploadQueue object is necessary.

Constructor Detail

UploadQueue

public UploadQueue(java.lang.String parentName,
                   Context context,
                   API api)
This is the constructor for an UploadQueue object. All parameters are necessary and essential to ensure that this object works properly.

Parameters:
parentName - Name of the parent activity the UploadQueue is being made in. This name is also used in making the serializable file where this UploadQueue will be stored
context - Context of the activity instantiating this object.
api - An API object that this UploadQueue object may utilize to upload data.
